title: Acetaminophen Level
description: This test measures the amount of acetaminophen in the blood. Acetaminophen is one of the most common medicines used in over-the-counter pain relievers and fever reducers.

title: Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI)
description: Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) is a medical imaging technique that uses a magnetic field and computer-generated radio waves to create detailed images of the organs and tissues in your body.

title: Methylmalonic Acid (MMA) Test

title: Uric Acid Test
description: This test measures the amount of uric acid in your blood or urine. Uric acid is a normal waste product that's made when the body breaks down chemicals called purines.

title: Celiac Disease Screening
description: Screening for celiac disease is typically not performed in average-risk persons. The standard method of diagnosing celiac disease is the tissue transglutaminase IgA test.
